Moscow Comes Under Attempted Drone AttackThe mayor of Moscow  Sergey Sobyanin  said there was “no major damage” following an attempted Ukrainian drone strike around 4am Monday morning. The drones crashed into non-residential buildings after the military suppressed them using electronic warfare means.Several drone fragments were found on Komsomolsky Prospekt in downtown Moscow  not far from the Defense Ministry’s main headquarters  a source in the emergency services told TASS news agency.While the drone itself hit a non-residential building  several windows in residential buildings in the area were reportedly blown out by the blast wave. There were no reports of casualties or injuries  but emergency services are working at the scene  with videos showing multiple police cars and ambulances.Subscribe toRT
